title: For Sale:  4 piece Modular Sleep System
postcontent:
The Modular Sleep System (MSS) is a modular sleeping bag used by the United States armed forces. These are genuine USGI obtained from a government auction.

The MSS consists of a camouflaged, waterproof, breathable Gore-Tex bivy cover, a lightweight patrol sleeping bag, and an intermediate cold weather sleeping bag. Compression sacks are included to store and carry the system.


The patrol bag provides cold weather protection from 35 to 50 degrees Fahrenheit. The intermediate bag provides cold weather protection from minus 5 to 35 degrees Fahrenheit. Together, the patrol bag and intermediate bags provide extreme cold weather protection in temperatures as low as minus 30 degrees Fahrenheit. The bivy cover can be used with each of three MSS configurations (patrol, intermediate, or combined) to be comparable with the environment in which the system is being used; the bivy cover provides environmental protection from wind and water.

I have a dozen of these, $75 each. If you buy 3 or more I will sell them at $70 per each.
I'm in Castle Rock but can meet you in the metro area.

PRICE REDUCTION!!!!!

As some of you probably know, the Ruger SP-101 is considered by many to be the finest .357 magnum revolver ever made for CCW or nightstand/glovebox duty.  Very SOLID construction handles the stoutest loads and minimizes felt recoil . . . 38+P feel like 22s out of this piece.  Small frame, 5 round cylinder and 3" barrel keep it compact . . . not a pocket gun, but carries well in a proper holster.

If you research reviews of the SP-101, you will see that it is one of the most popular revolvers out there . . . but due to overwhelming demand, quality control has suffered over the past few years . . . fear not, this one is an early model, back when they took their time putting them together, and fit and function are PERFECT.  You will not be disappointed with this piece at all.

Small frame makes it a good choice for individuals with smaller hands.  If you are recoil sensitive, it will also fire .38 Special.  Very accurate, reliable, durable gun in excellent overall condition.  Has been stored in a safe for the past ten years and rarely shot.  Just took it to the range last week and it ran great.

title: For Sale:  Marlin Model 1894 - .44 Caliber Magnum Lever Action Rifle
location: Los Angeles County City of Redondo Beach, Los Angeles, California
postcontent:
Marlin Model 1894 - .44 Mag. / .44 Spl., cal., Model 1894 with addition of cross bolt and hammer block safety, 20 in. barrel, 10 shot tube mag., adj. sights, straight grip walnut stock and forearm, 6lbs. Manufactured in 1983. Hot Flash refinishing done in 2013 cost $199.00.

The Marlin Model 1894 is a lever-action repeating rifle introduced in 1894 by the Marlin Firearms Company of North Haven, Connecticut. At its introduction the rifle came with a 24-inch barrel and was chambers a .44 Magnum. Rechambered variants remain in production today.


Marlin produced its first lever-action repeating rifle as the Model 1881, made for powerful hunting rounds. This was followed by the model of 1888 which was a top eject action like the 1881 with several improvements, most important was the incorporation of a locking lug locking the breach. It was chambered in the WCF (Winchester centerfire) family of cartridges originally developed for the Winchester 1873 rifle, 44WCF, 38WCF & 32WCF also known as the 44/40, 38/40 & 32/20. The Model 1889 that followed was the first lever action rifle to have a solid top with side ejection of spent cartridges. This model was chambered for the same cartridges as the 1888. Design improvements to the Model 1889, such as a one-piece trigger and a two-piece firing pin to prevent the rifle from firing unless the finger lever was fully closed or if the locking lug were missing, resulted in the Model 1894. Additionally, the finger lever lock of the Model 1889 was eliminated on the Model 1894 and replaced by a latch built into the lever itself.

I have shot less than one 30 round magazine through this AR.

About the Custom Tactical Billet AR15.

This AR15 comes with both a billet upper and lower receiver.

Lower Receiver:

This is a Mag Tactical Systems Gen 4 Lower.
These are Top of the line lowers.
They are also 35% lighter than a standard lower.  How do they do this?
Mag Tactical Systems use a Proprietary Magnesium/Aluminum alloy.  

Not only are they 35% lighter they are stronger.
They have reinforced trigger & hammer axle pin placement points.
Their front pivot pins are reinforced to eliminate any fracturing during torque when receiver is in the break down position.
So yes they are lighter and stronger where it matters.

The Lower also has an the larger integrated winter trigger guard.  This not only looks cleaner but adds strength to the lower.


Upper Receiver:

This Billet Upper is made from 7075 Aluminum.  
7075 is almost twice as strong as the average forger 6061 upper.  Not only is this aluminum stronger this receiver is much thicker than the standard forged receiver.
So not only is this billet upper stronger it looks tough as nails.

Barrel:

This is a 16” M4 Stainless Steel 1X9 twist barrel with M4 cut Nitride coated barrel extension. 
This Barrel is manufactured in the U.S.A.  It is made from US certified 416r Stainless steel. 
This is a top of the line Barrel.



Some of the upgrades over a standard AR15 other than those mentioned above:


Free Float Barrel:  	Free Floated Barrels are used for only the most accurate of rifles.  By free-				floating a barrels you isolate the barrel from any outside forces normally 					associated with most AR15's. The hand guards on a standard barrels apply force 				to a barrel when gripped.  This cause the barrel to flex or move ever so slightly.  				Ever so slightly amounts to ever so big at 100+ yards.  A barrels that is free 				floated does not have outside forces working against it and will shoot straight 				every time. 


Mid-length Free Floated Quad Rail: The quad rail allows for the operator to mount a slew 							of additions accessories to there weapons platform. This mid 						length Quad rail is also longer than the standard Carbine length 						hand guard allowing for more room to mount your accessories like 					a Bi-pod, Light, front sight and optics. This stock was given enough 					weight to help balance out the normally muzzle heavy feel associated 					with negative pitch buttstocks.  This stock also transforms into three 					different stocks by simple removing or adding the transformable  pieces 					to your custom feel.

 Tactical Charging handle:  This allows the shooter a larger surface to grap when charging the AR15.  				This also makes it much easier to charge the weapon when wearing 					gloves in cold weather.

Magpul Moe Pistol Grip: The MOE Grip provides Magpul quality, feel, and durability for the AR15 Pistol grip. The ergonomic, hand filling design combines aggressive texturing with storage core capability. 

Ambidextrous tactical end plate:  Allows for a sling to be attached to either the right or left of  the AR15.

Taurus PT 92 AF 9mm
Trying to slim down my collection to be more focused, and I am selling my Taurus.

I really like the double or single action style trigger on these style guns, and in a full sized high capacity pistol, makes it alot of fun to take to the range, or use for self defense.  While the gun itself was light enough to conceal carry if you dressed appropriately, it is a full sized gun, and the weight of a fully loaded mag make this not very practical for that purpose, but I can attest that it can be done.  

It comes with a set of Hougue grips which really improve the hold on the gun for someone with small to midsized hands like me.  I also have a set of Pachmeyr grips for it somewhere that were a bit bulkier, and if I can find them, they will go with as well.
It comes with the factory box and factory 15 round mag with the gun at this price.

 If you are interested, I am selling separately 1 each Ramline and Mecgar 17 rounds magazines.  They make up to a 19 round magazine now that still fits inside the grip without overhanging if you want the ultimate in high capacity, although you may have to go the gunshow and pay the big $$ to find them these days.

I also have a Bianchi Shadow II 3 slot pancake holster (Model 7 Size 19 Part # 18656) which fits the Taurus models 92 and 99, and Berretta 92/96D Brigadier, 92/96F Centurion, 92F, 92FCM, 96F models

If you want all of it, I can bundle it all together as well, otherwise I'll sell the accessories after the pistol sells.

If you don't know the story behind the Taurus Models 92 and 99 and why it looks so close to the Beretta Model 92.
